\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
The 4% Rule for Retirement (FIRE)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This rule suggests that if you spend 4% of your assets in your initial year
 of retirement and then adjust for inflation each year going forward, you
 will be unlikely run out of your money.
 If you want to spend 40k per year, you would need 1M to adhere this 4%
 rule.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This rule is alternatively described as the requirement to have 25 years
 worth of spending in your portfolio to afford retirement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
However, if you're planning to retire early, it may not be the best rule
 to follow.
 Especially if your retirement period is longer than 30 years.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
